Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.82,0:00:03.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's begin class.\N{\rChinese}好的，开始上课。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.88,0:00:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,And today we are discussing whether or not Trump will win in November.\N{\rChinese}今天我们讨论特朗普是否会在十一月赢得选举。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,And I'm making the prediction that he will win in November\N{\rChinese}我预测他会在十一月赢得选举。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.34,0:00:14.56,English,,0,0,0,,and that\N{\rChinese}以及那点
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,he will pick Nikki Haley as his vice president.\N{\rChinese}他将挑选尼基·海利为副总统。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.06,0:00:21.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let me make you the argument today.\N{\rChinese}好了，接下来我给你们讲个论点。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:27.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's first discuss why Biden won in 2020\N{\rChinese}好的，先来讨论一下拜登在2020年赢得选举的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.32,0:00:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,and why it's possible\N{\rChinese}然后再说说今年他可能会输的可能性。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.14,0:00:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,that he may lose this year.\N{\rChinese}（此处可补充）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so in 2020,\N{\rChinese}好的，2020年是……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.46,0:00:39.40,English,,0,0,0,,it was a very special year in American politics\N{\rChinese}那一年美国政治格局特别特殊……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.40,0:00:42.26,English,,0,0,0,,because it was a larger,\N{\rChinese}因为投票人数比往年多……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:46.96,English,,0,0,0,,it was the largest turnout in American history since about 1900.\N{\rChinese}自1900年以来，美国历史上最大的投票率。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.80,0:00:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so 74 million people voted for Trump.\N{\rChinese}好，74万投票给特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.22,0:00:55.08,English,,0,0,0,,For Biden, 81 million people voted for him.\N{\rChinese}81万投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.42,0:01:01.20,English,,0,0,0,,And two out of every three American adults came out to vote.\N{\rChinese}并且每三位美国成年人中有两位投票。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:04.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so it was the largest turnout in American history.\N{\rChinese}好，2020年是美国历史上最大的投票率。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.62,0:01:11.30,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't, it sounds like a very lopsided victory for Biden,\N{\rChinese}听起来像是拜登的绝对大胜。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.52,0:01:13.22,English,,0,0,0,,81 million versus 74 million.\N{\rChinese}8100万对比7400万。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.48,0:01:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,But because America has an electoral college system,\N{\rChinese}但因为美国有选举团制度，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.92,0:01:21.70,English,,0,0,0,,which is not director -elected,\N{\rChinese}它不是直接选举的。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:23.40,English,,0,0,0,,it's not a democratic democracy, actually,\N{\rChinese}它并不是一次真正的民主投票，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.46,0:01:28.42,English,,0,0,0,,the margin of victory was only 65,000 votes.\N{\rChinese}胜利差距仅有65,000票。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.56,0:01:34.46,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning that if 65,000 people in key battleground states flipped their votes,\N{\rChinese}也就是说，如果关键摇摆州的65,000人投票翻转，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:36.14,English,,0,0,0,,then Trump would have won.\N{\rChinese}然后特朗普就赢了。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.40,0:01:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the margin of victory was very, very close,\N{\rChinese}好的，胜利差距非常非常接近，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.66,0:01:44.18,English,,0,0,0,,as is usually the case in highly contested American elections.\N{\rChinese}正如在高度竞争的美国选举中常见的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.86,0:01:48.28,English,,0,0,0,,So let's understand the coalition that\N{\rChinese}于是我们来了解这个联盟
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.28,0:01:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,brought Biden into the White House.\N{\rChinese}把拜登送进白宫。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.68,0:01:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so\N{\rChinese}好的，所以。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:57.96,English,,0,0,0,,the first major component of this coalition are black people.\N{\rChinese}第一大组成部分是黑人。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.80,0:02:02.68,English,,0,0,0,,91% of all blacks voted for Biden.\N{\rChinese}91%的黑人投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.80,0:02:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,Only 8% voted for Trump.\N{\rChinese}仅有8%投票给特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.76,0:02:08.42,English,,0,0,0,,That's a huge majority for Biden.\N{\rChinese}这对拜登来说是大多数。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.20,0:02:13.92,English,,0,0,0,,So why did so many black people vote for Biden in 2020?\N{\rChinese}那么，为什么那么多的黑人在2020年投票给拜登？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,Well, first of all, it's because\N{\rChinese}首先，原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.40,0:02:21.60,English,,0,0,0,,Biden was Obama's vice president for eight years.\N{\rChinese}拜登曾是奥巴马的副总统八年。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.80,0:02:26.82,English,,0,0,0,,And so a lot of older black people had a certain loyalty to him.\N{\rChinese}于是很多年长的黑人对他有一定的忠诚。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.06,0:02:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, they felt that we owe this man because\N{\rChinese}好的，他们觉得我们欠这位先生，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:35.08,English,,0,0,0,,he served loyally to our man, Barack Obama, for eight years.\N{\rChinese}他忠诚地为我们的男人巴拉克·奥巴马服务了八年。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.26,0:02:37.76,English,,0,0,0,,And so now we must bring him into the White House.\N{\rChinese}于是现在我们必须把他带进白宫。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.44,0:02:40.80,English,,0,0,0,,But this year, the debt is paid off, right?\N{\rChinese}但今年债务已付清，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,So they won't feel so loyal to Biden.\N{\rChinese}于是他们对拜登的忠诚度就不那么高了。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:46.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Also in 2020,\N{\rChinese}好的。还有在2020年，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:50.10,English,,0,0,0,,there's something called a George Floyd protest.\N{\rChinese}有个叫做“乔治·弗洛伊德”抗议的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.64,0:02:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,So what happened was that\N{\rChinese}于是发生的事是这样：
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:02:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,in May 2020,\N{\rChinese}2020年5月，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.68,0:02:59.62,English,,0,0,0,,a black man in Minneapolis, George Floyd,\N{\rChinese}明尼阿波利斯的黑人乔治·弗洛伊德
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,he was strangled to death by a white police officer.\N{\rChinese}他被一名白人警察扼住喉咙致死。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.82,0:03:07.38,English,,0,0,0,,It was captured on video and it caused a national uproar.\N{\rChinese}它被拍成视频并引发全国性骚乱。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, there were riots\N{\rChinese}实际上，发生了骚乱
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,and protests throughout the country.\N{\rChinese}并在全国掀起示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:16.12,English,,0,0,0,,And Trump came out and did this.\N{\rChinese}随后特朗普出现并这么做了。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.14,0:03:19.04,English,,0,0,0,,He did not acknowledge the pain that\N{\rChinese}他没有承认那份痛感
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,black people felt because of this death.\N{\rChinese}黑人因这起死亡事件而产生感受。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.62,0:03:27.12,English,,0,0,0,,And so black people felt antipathy towards Trump. Okay.\N{\rChinese}于是黑人对特朗普产生了反感。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.46,0:03:33.08,English,,0,0,0,,So these are the two major reasons why black people voted for Biden in 2020.\N{\rChinese}所以这两点是黑人在2020年投票给拜登的主要原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:36.50,English,,0,0,0,,But this year,\N{\rChinese}但今年，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.04,0:03:39.46,English,,0,0,0,,Trump's not in office, right?\N{\rChinese}特朗普已经不在任了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:41.86,English,,0,0,0,,Biden's in office. So black people are asking the question,\N{\rChinese}拜登在任。于是黑人们在问……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.18,0:03:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,what has Biden done for us these past four years?\N{\rChinese}拜登过去四年为我们做了什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:50.08,English,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, the answer is not that much.\N{\rChinese}不幸的是，答案并不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.18,0:03:53.00,English,,0,0,0,,And in fact, you can make the argument that\N{\rChinese}而且，你可以这样论证：
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,Biden has really hurt the standard of living of black people.\N{\rChinese}拜登确实让黑人生活水平下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.42,0:04:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because inflation has gone up.\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为通胀上涨了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:05.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. When inflation goes up,\N{\rChinese}好的。当通胀上涨时，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.46,0:04:08.62,English,,0,0,0,,it usually hurts poor people the most.\N{\rChinese}它通常最伤害的是贫困人群。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.74,0:04:10.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. The standard of living goes way down.\N{\rChinese}好的，生活水平大幅下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,Also, illegal immigration\N{\rChinese}另外，非法移民也在增加。好。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.40,0:04:16.62,English,,0,0,0,,has gone up. Okay.\N{\rChinese}于是，在2020年，特朗普离任时。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.84,0:04:19.84,English,,0,0,0,,So in 2020, when Trump left office,\N{\rChinese}So in 2020, whenTrump left office,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.04,0:04:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,there were about 10 million illegal immigrants in America.\N{\rChinese}美国有大约一千万非法移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.48,0:04:26.56,English,,0,0,0,,Now there are 20 million illegal immigrants in America.\N{\rChinese}现在美国有两千万非法移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.74,0:04:31.00,English,,0,0,0,,And it seems like Biden's doing nothing to stop this trend.\N{\rChinese}看起来拜登什么也没做来阻止这个趋势。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:34.78,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, when illegal immigrants come to the country,\N{\rChinese}当然，非法移民来到这个国家时，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:37.50,English,,0,0,0,,they usually take the jobs of poor people.\N{\rChinese}他们通常抢走穷人的工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.62,0:04:38.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. They bring wages down.\N{\rChinese}于是工资就下降了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.12,0:04:40.88,English,,0,0,0,,And that again hurts black people.\N{\rChinese}又一次又伤害了黑人。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,And then third is Ukraine.\N{\rChinese}接着第三点是乌克兰。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:48.68,English,,0,0,0,,So while the standard of living for black people\N{\rChinese}于是黑人生活水平下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:51.14,English,,0,0,0,,and other poor people in America are going down,\N{\rChinese}以及美国其他贫困人群也在下降，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.38,0:04:56.56,English,,0,0,0,,America is sending tens of billions of dollars to Ukraine to fight a war\N{\rChinese}美国向乌克兰拨出数百亿美元以作战斗，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:05:00.54,English,,0,0,0,,that has nothing to do with America.\N{\rChinese}这与美国无关。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.96,0:05:04.56,English,,0,0,0,,So many Americans see this as just bad leadership.\N{\rChinese}于是许多美国人把这看成只是糟糕的领导。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.80,0:05:06.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So that's black people.\N{\rChinese}好的。那就是黑人。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.86,0:05:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,And recent polls show that\N{\rChinese}而最近的民调显示……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.48,0:05:15.46,English,,0,0,0,,actually Biden's lead with black people is not a bad thing.\N{\rChinese}实际上拜登在黑人选民中的领先并不算坏事。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.46,0:05:17.28,English,,0,0,0,,Not as much as it was in 2020.\N{\rChinese}比2020年少了不少。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.50,0:05:19.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So this lead is going down.\N{\rChinese}好的，这个领先正在下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.30,0:05:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,Young people. Okay.\N{\rChinese}年轻人。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.48,0:05:26.46,English,,0,0,0,,Well, young people tend to vote Democratic in all elections.\N{\rChinese}嗯，年轻人往往在各次选举中投票给民主党。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.48,0:05:32.22,English,,0,0,0,,And they were extremely galvanized to vote in 2020\N{\rChinese}他们在2020年投票热情高涨。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:37.26,English,,0,0,0,,because they saw Trump as this very hateful racist\N{\rChinese}因为他们把特朗普视为极其可恨的种族主义者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:38.66,English,,0,0,0,,that they must remove from office.\N{\rChinese}他必须从职务上移除。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,Right. And they were driven to believe this because of the George Floyd protests.\N{\rChinese}对，正因乔治·弗洛伊德示威而产生此信念。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:46.14,English,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, this year,\N{\rChinese}不幸的是，今年，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:50.46,English,,0,0,0,,young people may not feel compelled to vote for Biden.\N{\rChinese}年轻人可能不再被迫投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:55.44,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, a lot of young people are choosing to sit out this election.\N{\rChinese}实际上，很多年轻人选择在这次选举中不投票。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:57.48,English,,0,0,0,,Why? You guys know?\N{\rChinese}为什么？你们知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.14,0:05:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,Gaza. Okay.\N{\rChinese}加沙。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:02.72,English,,0,0,0,,So as you know, right now,\N{\rChinese}所以正如你们所知，现在是……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.72,0:06:04.46,English,,0,0,0,,throughout America on college campuses,\N{\rChinese}在美国各大专校园里，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.74,0:06:07.68,English,,0,0,0,,young people are protesting the war in Gaza.\N{\rChinese}年轻人正在抗议加沙战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.06,0:06:12.20,English,,0,0,0,,So these young people are not going to vote for Trump.\N{\rChinese}于是这些年轻人不会投票给特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.28,0:06:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. But\N{\rChinese}好的。但
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:15.32,English,,0,0,0,,they probably will not vote for Biden as\N{\rChinese}他们大概不会投票给拜登，作为对美国通过以色列政策的抗议。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.32,0:06:19.56,English,,0,0,0,,a protest against American policy via the Israel.\N{\rChinese}a protest against American policy via the Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Now let's look at the college educated.\N{\rChinese}好的。现在我们来看看受过大学教育的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:27.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So 70% of people with college degrees voted for Biden.\N{\rChinese}好的。所以70%的大学学历者投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.66,0:06:34.32,English,,0,0,0,,These are what we call the coastal elite.\N{\rChinese}这些就是我们所说的海岸精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.46,0:06:38.46,English,,0,0,0,,Right. The coastal professional managerial elite.\N{\rChinese}右。海岸专业管理精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:42.16,English,,0,0,0,,And they usually overwhelmingly vote Democratic.\N{\rChinese}他们通常压倒性投票给民主党。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.16,0:06:44.26,English,,0,0,0,,And this year, they will still say the same.\N{\rChinese}今年他们仍会这么说。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.64,0:06:47.02,English,,0,0,0,,But they will be less enthusiastic\N{\rChinese}但他们的热情会稍低
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.02,0:06:51.74,English,,0,0,0,,because of what they perceive to be poor global leadership.\N{\rChinese}因为他们认为全球领导力不足
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Biden under Biden's watch, Ukraine blew up.\N{\rChinese}好的。拜登在位时，乌克兰爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:06:57.62,English,,0,0,0,,But so did Gaza.\N{\rChinese}但加沙也一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.32,0:07:01.20,English,,0,0,0,,And many are starting to feel that it's because\N{\rChinese}而且许多人开始觉得这正是因为……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,Biden comes across as too old,\N{\rChinese}拜登给人的印象太老了，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.22,0:07:07.90,English,,0,0,0,,too weak, and too feeble to stand against Putin.\N{\rChinese}太弱，太脆弱，无法与普京抗衡。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.40,0:07:12.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So college educated people will still vote for Biden.\N{\rChinese}好的。所以受过大学教育的人仍会投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.14,0:07:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,So overwhelmingly vote Democratic. That is the core Democratic base.\N{\rChinese}于是大多数投票给民主党。这就是核心民主党基础。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:18.28,English,,0,0,0,,But they'll be less enthusiastic about Biden.\N{\rChinese}但他们对拜登的热情会稍低。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.44,0:07:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,And they'll vote primarily against Trump.\N{\rChinese}他们主要会投票给普京。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.04,0:07:24.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Woman. Okay.\N{\rChinese}好的。女人。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:30.28,English,,0,0,0,,So 54% of women voted for Biden.\N{\rChinese}于是54%的女性投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,44% voted for Trump.\N{\rChinese}44%投票给特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:35.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And again, because\N{\rChinese}好。再一次，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:39.60,English,,0,0,0,,Trump is seen as this hateful figure.\N{\rChinese}特朗普被视为这位可恨的形象。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.40,0:07:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,We expect that\N{\rChinese}我们预期它会。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.36,0:07:45.24,English,,0,0,0,,woman will still consistently vote Democratic this year.\N{\rChinese}该女子今年仍将持续投票给民主党。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:48.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And also because of abortion issues.\N{\rChinese}好的。还有因为生育问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.92,0:07:52.68,English,,0,0,0,,Right. So women are very passionate about abortion.\N{\rChinese}对。于是女性对生育问题非常热情。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:56.32,English,,0,0,0,,And they will come out and vote for Biden to ensure\N{\rChinese}他们会出来投票给拜登以确保
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.32,0:07:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,that abortion rights are protected.\N{\rChinese}已保障生育权利。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:02.40,English,,0,0,0,,Last, let's look at suburban voters.\N{\rChinese}最后，让我们看一下郊区选民。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.54,0:08:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So the suburbs.\N{\rChinese}好的。于是郊区。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.32,0:08:07.58,English,,0,0,0,,The suburbs are between the cities, the urban areas, and the rural areas.\N{\rChinese}郊区位于城市、都市区与乡村之间。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Cities, urban areas, overwhelmingly support the Democratic Party.\N{\rChinese}好的。城市、都市区大多支持民主党。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.96,0:08:17.16,English,,0,0,0,,Rural areas overwhelmingly support the Republican Party.\N{\rChinese}乡村区大多支持共和党。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,So the suburbs are where the battleground is.\N{\rChinese}郊区就是战场所在。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:23.34,English,,0,0,0,,And so if you look at 19,\N{\rChinese}于是如果你看2019年，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.88,0:08:26.82,English,,0,0,0,,sorry, 2016,\N{\rChinese}抱歉，2016年。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.82,0:08:29.96,English,,0,0,0,,when Trump defeated Hillary Clinton,\N{\rChinese}当特朗普击败希拉里·克林顿时
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.36,0:08:33.82,English,,0,0,0,,only 45% of\N{\rChinese}仅有45%的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.42,0:08:36.58,English,,0,0,0,,the suburbs voted for Clinton.\N{\rChinese}郊区投票给克林顿
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.58,0:08:40.40,English,,0,0,0,,Which allowed Trump to defeat her in the election.\N{\rChinese}这使得特朗普在选举中击败她。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.58,0:08:44.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Now, what's interesting is that in 2020,\N{\rChinese}好的。接下来有趣的是在2020年，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.24,0:08:46.88,English,,0,0,0,,this flipped and\N{\rChinese}这一点发生了翻转。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:52.16,English,,0,0,0,,54% of suburban voters voted for Biden.\N{\rChinese}郊区选民中有54%投票给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.60,0:08:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,That's a flip of 2 million voters.\N{\rChinese}这相当于两百万人投票翻转。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.14,0:08:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So in elections,\N{\rChinese}好，回到选举上。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:02.50,English,,0,0,0,,usually it's a suburban vote that\N{\rChinese}通常是郊区选票决定选举，因为有摇摆选民。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.50,0:09:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,determines the election because there's swing voters.\N{\rChinese}好的。于是我们来快速看看为什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}Okay. So
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:10.52,English,,0,0,0,,for Trump to win this year,\N{\rChinese}为了让特朗普今年赢得胜利，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.70,0:09:13.90,English,,0,0,0,,he needs to win the suburban vote.\N{\rChinese}他需要赢得郊区选票。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,He won that in 2016.\N{\rChinese}他在2016年赢得了那一票。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:18.58,English,,0,0,0,,He lost that in 2020. Okay.\N{\rChinese}他在2020年输了那一票。好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.68,0:09:20.90,English,,0,0,0,,So let's examine very\N{\rChinese}于是我们来快速看看原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,quickly why the\N{\rChinese}quickly why the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.64,0:09:27.62,English,,0,0,0,,suburbs went Biden in 2020.\N{\rChinese}郊区在2020年投给拜登。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And there are three major reasons.\N{\rChinese}好的，还有三个主要原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,The first is the media narrative. So\N{\rChinese}第一个是媒体叙事。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:40.16,English,,0,0,0,,what's happening throughout Trump's presidency\N{\rChinese}特朗普执政期间发生的事
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,is basically the entire mainstream media got together\N{\rChinese}基本上，主流媒体聚在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:48.38,English,,0,0,0,,and criticized Trump.\N{\rChinese}并批评特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.70,0:09:52.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So the first major criticism of Trump, if you remember,\N{\rChinese}好的。第一个主要批评是，若你记得，是他是俄国资产。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,is he was a Russian asset.\N{\rChinese}好的。第一个主要批评是，若你记得，是他是俄国资产。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.22,0:09:58.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. He was a paid Putin puppet.\N{\rChinese}好的。他是付费的普京傀儡。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.54,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, that was just a complete lie.\N{\rChinese}当然，那只是完全的谎言。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.70,0:10:02.92,English,,0,0,0,,What we call Russiagate. Okay.\N{\rChinese}我们称之为俄案。好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:05.56,English,,0,0,0,,But then they start to say that\N{\rChinese}但随后他们开始说……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,Trump was a divisive figure.\N{\rChinese}特朗普是一个分裂的形象。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:10.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.38,0:10:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,this idea caught\N{\rChinese}这个想法在郊区抓住了想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:16.90,English,,0,0,0,,the imagination of the suburbs.\N{\rChinese}这个想法在郊区抓住了想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:20.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Because if you live in the suburbs, you tend to be middle class.\N{\rChinese}好的。因为如果你住在郊区，你往往属于中产阶层。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.54,0:10:22.56,English,,0,0,0,,You tend to be pretty wealthy and well educated.\N{\rChinese}你往往会相当富裕且受过良好教育。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,So you like the status quo. You want a leader who's conservative\N{\rChinese}于是你喜欢现状。你想要一个保守的领袖
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.66,0:10:29.48,English,,0,0,0,,and who's a unifier.\N{\rChinese}并且是个统一者
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:32.66,English,,0,0,0,,And throughout the Trump presidency, we saw that.\N{\rChinese}在整个特朗普任期里我们都看见了这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.66,0:10:35.04,English,,0,0,0,,We saw the polarization of politics.\N{\rChinese}我们看到了政治的两极化。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,The left and the right hate each other and they fought all the time.\N{\rChinese}左翼与右翼互相仇恨，时常争斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.16,0:10:44.58,English,,0,0,0,,And what really showed this was the George Floyd protests.\N{\rChinese}而真正体现这一点的是乔治·弗洛伊德示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.32,0:10:49.96,English,,0,0,0,,So you had protesters rioting in the streets.\N{\rChinese}于是街头有示威者起义。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.42,0:10:54.46,English,,0,0,0,,And Trump was like, let's send in the military to crush the protesters.\N{\rChinese}于是特朗普说，派军队去镇压示威者。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:10:58.90,English,,0,0,0,,And so people in the suburbs were very worried about this.\N{\rChinese}于是郊区的人对此很担心。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.02,0:11:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,They thought that a leader, the president, should be a uniter.\N{\rChinese}他们认为，领袖、总统应是团结者。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.36,0:11:07.96,English,,0,0,0,,Right. And Biden came across as extremely steady,\N{\rChinese}对，拜登给人极稳重之感，像个老牌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.20,0:11:11.24,English,,0,0,0,,as very establishment, as someone who\N{\rChinese}他是个……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.24,0:11:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,could unite both the Republican Party and the Democratic Party.\N{\rChinese}可以把共和党和民主党都团结起来。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.00,0:11:18.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. That was his perception in 2020.\N{\rChinese}好的。那是他在2020年的看法。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.48,0:11:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first major reason why the suburbs went Biden.\N{\rChinese}这就是郊区投票给拜登的首要原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.80,0:11:25.78,English,,0,0,0,,Second was the pandemic.\N{\rChinese}第二点是疫情。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.16,0:11:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,So as you know, COVID hit the United States.\N{\rChinese}正如你所知，COVID席卷美国。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.92,0:11:33.98,English,,0,0,0,,And the suburbs were extremely freaked out about this\N{\rChinese}郊区对此极为惊慌。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.98,0:11:36.38,English,,0,0,0,,because they tend to have children who go to school.\N{\rChinese}因为他们往往有孩子上学。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.38,0:11:39.40,English,,0,0,0,,They tend to be older.\N{\rChinese}他们往往年纪大。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.70,0:11:42.00,English,,0,0,0,,And they thought that\N{\rChinese}他们认为这样就行了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.00,0:11:46.28,English,,0,0,0,,Trump's handling of the pandemic was very incompetent.\N{\rChinese}特朗普对疫情的处理非常不称职。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:49.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. He was an outsider,\N{\rChinese}好的。他是个外来人，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.76,0:11:53.66,English,,0,0,0,,a political outsider. But that meant he could not get things done in Washington.\N{\rChinese}但这意味着他在华盛办事不顺利。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So that's the second problem with Trump.\N{\rChinese}好的。那就是特朗普的第二个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:11:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,And the third reason why\N{\rChinese}还有第三个原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.70,0:12:05.34,English,,0,0,0,,the suburbs went Biden is Kamala Harris.\N{\rChinese}郊区投给拜登的是卡玛拉·哈里斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:08.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And this is key.\N{\rChinese}好的。关键点来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,Biden picked Kamala Harris to\N{\rChinese}拜登挑选卡玛拉·哈里斯为副总统。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.44,0:12:15.40,English,,0,0,0,,be his vice president.\N{\rChinese}be his vice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:17.30,English,,0,0,0,,To be his running mate.\N{\rChinese}成为他的竞选搭档。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.62,0:12:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,And Kamala Harris, let me tell you a little about Kamala Harris.\N{\rChinese}我来稍微介绍一下卡玛拉·哈里斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:24.10,English,,0,0,0,,Her father is Jamaican.\N{\rChinese}她的父亲是牙买加人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.14,0:12:28.60,English,,0,0,0,,Her mother is Indian. And she has a younger sister.\N{\rChinese}她的母亲是印度人，她还有个妹妹。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.28,0:12:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,But she was young.\N{\rChinese}但她还很年轻。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.32,0:12:33.30,English,,0,0,0,,Her dad left the family.\N{\rChinese}她的父亲离开了家。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:38.26,English,,0,0,0,,So her mom raised the two girls by herself.\N{\rChinese}她的妈妈独自抚养了这两个女孩。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.14,0:12:42.88,English,,0,0,0,,And Kamala Harris is an extremely accomplished person.\N{\rChinese}卡玛拉·哈里斯是一位极为出色的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.56,0:12:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,She went to Stanford.\N{\rChinese}她曾就读过斯坦福大学。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:49.14,English,,0,0,0,,Then she became Attorney General of California.\N{\rChinese}然后她成为加利福尼亚州总检察长。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.50,0:12:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,Then became a U.S.\N{\rChinese}随后她成为美国参议员。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:12:52.42,English,,0,0,0,,Senator. Okay. And\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:55.98,English,,0,0,0,,there are three reasons why the suburbs love Kamala Harris.\N{\rChinese}有三个原因解释为什么郊区人喜欢卡玛拉·哈里斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:12:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. First of all,\N{\rChinese}好的。首先，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:13:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,like us.\N{\rChinese}像我们一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:06.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Meaning like she comes across as someone who\N{\rChinese}好的。也就是说她给人的印象是……
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.68,0:13:08.54,English,,0,0,0,,speaks and\N{\rChinese}说话像郊区人一样
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:11.90,English,,0,0,0,,thinks like people in the suburbs.\N{\rChinese}思考像郊区人一样
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.08,0:13:15.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Well educated, articulate,\N{\rChinese}受过良好教育，口才好，聪明，保守。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.78,0:13:17.18,English,,0,0,0,,smart, conservative.\N{\rChinese}受过良好教育，口才好，聪明，保守。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.46,0:13:22.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Second is she's seen as very establishment.\N{\rChinese}好的。第二点是她被视为非常建制派。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.24,0:13:25.88,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning that she's not liberal.\N{\rChinese}也就是说她不是自由派。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:29.36,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, when she was Attorney General of California,\N{\rChinese}事实上，她在加州总检察官任期内，刑事案件处理非常严厉。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.78,0:13:32.32,English,,0,0,0,,she was extremely tough on crime.\N{\rChinese}她在加州总检察官任期内，刑事案件处理非常严厉。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,She was trying to send as many people to jail as possible.\N{\rChinese}她试着把尽可能多的人送进监狱。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.88,0:13:39.98,English,,0,0,0,,And sometimes, quite honestly, some of these people were innocent.\N{\rChinese}有时，真诚地说，其中有些人是无辜的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.28,0:13:42.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And she still sent them to jail.\N{\rChinese}好的。她还是把他们送进监狱。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.54,0:13:45.86,English,,0,0,0,,She was very controversial as Attorney General.\N{\rChinese}她在加州总检察官任期内颇具争议。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.56,0:13:48.10,English,,0,0,0,,But guess what, guys?\N{\rChinese}但你猜怎么了，伙计们？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.42,0:13:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,People in the suburbs like tough on crime.\N{\rChinese}郊区的人喜欢对犯罪严厉。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.58,0:13:53.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. They want safety.\N{\rChinese}好的。他们想要安全。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:54.80,English,,0,0,0,,They want security. They have kids.\N{\rChinese}他们想要安全。孩子们在。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:13:57.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:14:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,the third reason why they like Kamala Harris is\N{\rChinese}第三个他们喜欢卡玛拉·哈里斯的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.08,0:14:03.88,English,,0,0,0,,because of the redemption story.\N{\rChinese}因为复兴的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.42,0:14:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,So, in 2019,\N{\rChinese}于是，2019年，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.46,0:14:14.08,English,,0,0,0,,there's a Democratic primary. Okay. This is when\N{\rChinese}有一次民主党初选。好的。那时
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:18.02,English,,0,0,0,,the Democrats try to\N{\rChinese}民主党人试图
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.02,0:14:20.88,English,,0,0,0,,get a nomination for the general election.\N{\rChinese}获得大选的提名。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.98,0:14:24.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And there was a lot of people who\N{\rChinese}好的，很多人争夺提名，包括乔·拜登和卡玛拉·哈里斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.60,0:14:28.88,English,,0,0,0,,are vying for the nomination, including Joe Biden and Kamala Harris.\N{\rChinese}在2019年6月，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,In June 2019,\N{\rChinese}In June 2019,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:35.14,English,,0,0,0,,there was the first Democratic debate.\N{\rChinese}有一次第一次民主党辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.08,0:14:39.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And at this point, Kamala Harris and\N{\rChinese}好的。此时，卡玛拉·哈里斯和乔·拜登被视为夺得提名的重磅候选人。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.02,0:14:44.08,English,,0,0,0,,Joe Biden were considered very heavy favorites to win the nomination.\N{\rChinese}Joe Biden were considered very heavy favorites to win the nomination.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,And in that first debate,\N{\rChinese}在那场第一次辩论中，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.74,0:14:51.12,English,,0,0,0,,Kamala Harris and Joe Biden got into a very serious fight.\N{\rChinese}卡玛拉·哈里斯和乔·拜登展开了一场激烈的争论。
