Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.96,0:29:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,basically decide US elections.\N{\rChinese}basically decideUS elections.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.62,0:29:39.40,English,,0,0,0,,And as vice president,\N{\rChinese}作为副总统，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.58,0:29:44.30,English,,0,0,0,,what she will be doing is advocating for war against Iran,\N{\rChinese}她将要做的就是倡导对伊朗的战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.56,0:29:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,which means that she's on the payroll\N{\rChinese}这意味着她已被列入名单中
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.71,0:29:52.96,English,,0,0,0,,of anti -Iranian forces in the United States.\N{\rChinese}在美国的反伊朗势力中。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.67,0:29:58.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, any questions?\N{\rChinese}好的？那还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.15,0:30:01.22,English,,0,0,0,,Anything you're not clear about right now?\N{\rChinese}现在你还有不明白的地方吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.80,0:30:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,What if she holds a grudge against Trump?\N{\rChinese}如果她对特朗普怀有怨恨呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.64,0:30:22.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so Jack asked a great question, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，杰克提出了一个很好的问题，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.20,0:30:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,He's like, what if Haley holds a grudge and says no, right?\N{\rChinese}他是这么说的：如果哈利对他有怨恨并且说不，怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.92,0:30:32.24,English,,0,0,0,,And quite honestly, she has been asked in the past,\N{\rChinese}而且说实话，她曾被问过，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.52,0:30:35.82,English,,0,0,0,,are you willing to serve as Trump's vice president?\N{\rChinese}你愿意当特朗普的副总统吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,And she's like, no, because he's a divider.\N{\rChinese}她回答说，愿意，因为他是个分裂者。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.82,0:30:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,He's divisive, and we need to move on from Trump, okay?\N{\rChinese}他是分裂的，我们需要从特朗普身上走开，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.40,0:30:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Do you guys remember in class,\N{\rChinese}好的。你们记得在课堂上，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.10,0:30:54.76,English,,0,0,0,,when we studied Trump, very closely, his personality?\N{\rChinese}当我们细细研究特朗普，他的个性格吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.54,0:30:58.84,English,,0,0,0,,We looked at his days in the WWE, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们回顾了他在WWE的日子，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.54,0:31:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,And there was a scene where Vince McMahon,\N{\rChinese}随后出现了一个场景，Vince McMahon，WWE的老板，亿万富翁，挑战特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.12,0:31:07.38,English,,0,0,0,,the owner of WWE, a billionaire, challenges Trump\N{\rChinese}the owner of WWE, a billionaire, challenges Trump
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.02,0:31:09.96,English,,0,0,0,,to a fight, right?\N{\rChinese}转成一场斗争，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.82,0:31:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,Well, guess what, guys? Politics is the same thing.\N{\rChinese}好，猜猜吧，伙计们？政治就是一样的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.24,0:31:15.74,English,,0,0,0,,It's all theater, okay?\N{\rChinese}全是戏剧，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:21.34,English,,0,0,0,,Politics is theater. What Nikki Haley\N{\rChinese}政治是戏剧。尼基·黑利
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.34,0:31:25.18,English,,0,0,0,,and Donald Trump are doing is pretending to be bitter enemies,\N{\rChinese}和唐纳德·特朗普正在假装成对手，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.36,0:31:29.56,English,,0,0,0,,so that their reconciliation will be\N{\rChinese}以便他们的和解能出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.56,0:31:32.20,English,,0,0,0,,so dramatic. You understand?\N{\rChinese}好戏剧。你明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.58,0:31:38.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, Nikki Haley served under Trump in the first administration,\N{\rChinese}于是，尼基·黑利在特朗普第一届任期服役，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.28,0:31:39.66,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So, from 2016 to 2018,\N{\rChinese}好？于是，从2016到2018，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.02,0:31:41.78,English,,0,0,0,,she was used to being a fighter. She was used to being an ambassador for Trump.\N{\rChinese}她习惯了当斗士。她习惯了当特朗普的使者。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.10,0:31:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,And everyone says that the two got along really well.\N{\rChinese}大家都说两人相处得很不错。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.48,0:31:48.56,English,,0,0,0,,In fact,\N{\rChinese}事实上，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.74,0:31:53.98,English,,0,0,0,,Trump was considering having her be his VP,\N{\rChinese}特朗普正在考虑让她担任副总统
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.30,0:31:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,running mate, in 2020.\N{\rChinese}2020年，他是竞选搭档。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.90,0:32:00.92,English,,0,0,0,,He was thinking of dropping Mike Pence and putting her on the ticket, okay?\N{\rChinese}他想把麦克·佩恩换掉，放上她，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.02,0:32:04.24,English,,0,0,0,,So, the two of them together actually have a great rapport.\N{\rChinese}于是，两人合在一起真的相处得很好。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.54,0:32:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,The two respect each other.\N{\rChinese}两人互相尊敬。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.96,0:32:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,They get along very well, okay? So, that's the first thing.\N{\rChinese}他们相处得很好，行吗？所以，这就是第一件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.58,0:32:10.18,English,,0,0,0,,Second thing is that,\N{\rChinese}第二件事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.82,0:32:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,the thing to know about very\N{\rChinese}关于非常成功的政治家的第一件事是
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.74,0:32:17.32,English,,0,0,0,,successful politicians is they are first\N{\rChinese}成功的政治家首先是
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.32,0:32:19.28,English,,0,0,0,,and foremost opportunists.\N{\rChinese}而且是最主要的机会主义者。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.54,0:32:21.40,English,,0,0,0,,They have no ideas.\N{\rChinese}他们没有主张。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.28,0:32:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,They have no principles.\N{\rChinese}他们没有原则。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.04,0:32:29.20,English,,0,0,0,,All they care about is political power, right?\N{\rChinese}他们只关心政治权力，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.60,0:32:32.84,English,,0,0,0,,So, why would Nikki Haley agree to be Vice President?\N{\rChinese}那么，尼基·海利为什么会同意做副总统？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.00,0:32:37.92,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.92,0:32:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,there's one step away from the presidency.\N{\rChinese}离总统一步之遥。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.84,0:32:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,presidency, do you understand? If anything happens to Trump, she's president.\N{\rChinese}总统，明白吗？只要特朗普有事，她就能当选。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.94,0:32:45.74,English,,0,0,0,,And in four years time, she can run as\N{\rChinese}四年后，她就能竞选。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.82,0:32:49.56,English,,0,0,0,,the Republican nominee for the presidency.\N{\rChinese}共和党总统候选人。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.80,0:32:53.66,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? So that's the thing you need to know about politicians.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？这就是你需要知道的关于政治家的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.52,0:32:56.46,English,,0,0,0,,All they care about is political power.\N{\rChinese}他们只关心政治权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.68,0:32:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,They will do anything to achieve political power.\N{\rChinese}他们会不择手段争取政治权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.76,0:33:02.64,English,,0,0,0,,They will sell their own mother to achieve political power.\N{\rChinese}他们会卖掉自己的母亲以争取政治权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.74,0:33:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,But it's the same thing for rich people.\N{\rChinese}但这对富人来说也是同样的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.32,0:33:05.66,English,,0,0,0,,Rich people love money.\N{\rChinese}富人爱钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.84,0:33:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,They will do anything to get money.\N{\rChinese}他们会不择手段争取钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.38,0:33:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,Sell their own mother, fine.\N{\rChinese}卖掉自己的母亲也行。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.62,0:33:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,Also, celebrities, famous people, right?\N{\rChinese}还有，明星、名人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.42,0:33:18.18,English,,0,0,0,,All they care about is fame. So, do you understand, Jack?\N{\rChinese}他们只在乎名声。所以，你明白了吗，杰克？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.04,0:33:21.12,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions?\N{\rChinese}还有别问吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.58,0:33:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,Is this clear to you guys?\N{\rChinese}这句话你们明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,Is there anything you're not clear about?\N{\rChinese}还有什么不明白的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.58,0:33:38.06,English,,0,0,0,,I'll explain further.\N{\rChinese}我再解释一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.24,0:33:44.02,English,,0,0,0,,Is there anything that\N{\rChinese}有什么可以
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.02,0:33:46.36,English,,0,0,0,,Biden could do before the election\N{\rChinese}拜登在选举前可以做的事
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.36,0:33:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,to have an advantage over Trump?\N{\rChinese}来占据优势于特朗普？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.50,0:33:54.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so Jack asked a great question, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，杰克刚刚问了个好问题，听着？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.72,0:33:58.44,English,,0,0,0,,Well, listen. Like,\N{\rChinese}嗯，听着。像是，我只要读新闻就能算出来，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.44,0:34:00.94,English,,0,0,0,,I can figure this out just by reading the news, right?\N{\rChinese}I can figure this out justby reading the news, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.34,0:34:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,Biden has an amazing team of extremely well -paid,\N{\rChinese}拜登拥有一支极其高薪、专业、经验丰富的战略团队与他合作。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.52,0:34:08.82,English,,0,0,0,,professional, experienced strategists working with him.\N{\rChinese}他们对此了如指掌，能洞察一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.88,0:34:11.46,English,,0,0,0,,They know this. They can see what's going on.\N{\rChinese}他们知道这一点，能看清局势。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.96,0:34:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, what can Biden do to\N{\rChinese}那么拜登能做什么来应对特朗普的策略或民调呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.06,0:34:19.46,English,,0,0,0,,counter Trump's strategy or the polls, okay?\N{\rChinese}答案是这样的：如果你看看2020年，…】
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.34,0:34:24.32,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is this. If you look at 2020,\N{\rChinese}And the answer is this. If you look at 2020,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.70,0:34:27.38,English,,0,0,0,,everyone thought\N{\rChinese}大家都认为
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.38,0:34:32.02,English,,0,0,0,,that Biden could not get the nomination, okay?\N{\rChinese}拜登能否获得提名？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.20,0:34:34.32,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because he lacks charisma.\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为他缺乏魅力。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:36.08,English,,0,0,0,,Nobody really likes him, okay?\N{\rChinese}没人真喜欢他，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.34,0:34:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,So, when Biden goes to school, he's not going to get the nomination.\N{\rChinese}于是，拜登去学校时，他还没拿到提名。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.36,0:34:40.30,English,,0,0,0,,He's going to speak. There's no one there to listen to him.\N{\rChinese}他会发言。那里没人听他说。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.36,0:34:44.86,English,,0,0,0,,He's boring, and he has no ideas, and he's old.\N{\rChinese}他很无聊，没想法，老了。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.12,0:34:50.26,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, Biden ran for president two times before, and he lost both times.\N{\rChinese}我说，拜登以前跑两次总统，两个都输了。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.42,0:34:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,And the reason why is he's not charismatic, and\N{\rChinese}原因是他不具魅力，且
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.40,0:34:55.38,English,,0,0,0,,he has no ideas, okay?\N{\rChinese}他没有想法，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.60,0:34:59.90,English,,0,0,0,,But Biden's like, nope, I'm going to stay in the race because I believe I can win.\N{\rChinese}但拜登说：不，我会继续参选，因为我相信能赢。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.12,0:35:03.80,English,,0,0,0,,And you ask him, Biden, what is your strategy?\N{\rChinese}你问他，拜登，你的策略是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.98,0:35:05.22,English,,0,0,0,,What is your reasoning going forward?\N{\rChinese}接下来你会怎么推理？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.42,0:35:07.58,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I'm going to win, okay?\N{\rChinese}我不知道，我会赢，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.80,0:35:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,So, if we were discussing this in 2020,\N{\rChinese}于是，如果我们在2020年讨论这个，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.90,0:35:15.42,English,,0,0,0,,in May and June,\N{\rChinese}在五月和六月，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.04,0:35:20.18,English,,0,0,0,,I would be like, Biden has no chance, okay?\N{\rChinese}我会说：拜登没机会，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.28,0:35:22.36,English,,0,0,0,,Because Trump's going to go out there and\N{\rChinese}因为特朗普会去那里…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.36,0:35:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,give speeches to 100,000 people, and\N{\rChinese}给十万人演讲，随后他们会爱上他，随后去投票，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.64,0:35:29.12,English,,0,0,0,,they're going to love him, and they're going to go and vote for him, okay?\N{\rChinese}拜登演讲，大家全都睡着。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.26,0:35:31.12,English,,0,0,0,,Biden gives a speech, everyone falls asleep.\N{\rChinese}Biden gives a speech,everyone falls asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.54,0:35:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,And under the debate stage,\N{\rChinese}在辩论阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.54,0:35:36.26,English,,0,0,0,,Trump will destroy Biden, okay?\N{\rChinese}特朗普会把拜登打败，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.94,0:35:40.56,English,,0,0,0,,So, I was sure that\N{\rChinese}于是，我确信
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.56,0:35:44.82,English,,0,0,0,,in May, April 2020,\N{\rChinese}五月，四月2020年，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.46,0:35:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,Biden had no chance.\N{\rChinese}拜登没有机会。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.40,0:35:52.04,English,,0,0,0,,But then what happened? Hey, the George Floyd protest happened.\N{\rChinese}然后发生了什么？嘿，乔治·弗洛伊德示威发生了。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.66,0:35:55.62,English,,0,0,0,,So all these young people who didn't really like Biden,\N{\rChinese}于是这些年轻人，之前不太喜欢拜登，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.76,0:35:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,they were now galvanized to go vote for him.\N{\rChinese}他们现在被激励去投票给他。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.18,0:36:01.14,English,,0,0,0,,All these black people, all these suburban voters,\N{\rChinese}这些黑人、郊区选民，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.28,0:36:05.30,English,,0,0,0,,they wanted Biden to win because they thought Trump was divisive, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们想拜登赢，因为觉得特朗普分裂，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.26,0:36:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,And then what happened? The pandemic happened.\N{\rChinese}然后发生了什么？疫情来了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.54,0:36:11.26,English,,0,0,0,,So, Trump couldn't go out to debate.\N{\rChinese}于是特朗普没能出场辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.76,0:36:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,Trump couldn't go out to campaign anymore.\N{\rChinese}特朗普再也没法外出竞选了。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.80,0:36:16.40,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? Biden could just sit in his basement\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？拜登可以在他地下室里坐着不动，没错吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.40,0:36:19.58,English,,0,0,0,,and do nothing, right?\N{\rChinese}and do nothing,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.86,0:36:23.04,English,,0,0,0,,Do you understand? So,\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.04,0:36:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,unfortunately, Biden learned the wrong lessons from 2020.\N{\rChinese}不幸的是，拜登从2020年学到了错误的经验。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.72,0:36:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,The lesson that he learned in 2020 is that, hey,\N{\rChinese}他在2020年学到的经验是，嘿，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.80,0:36:33.72,English,,0,0,0,,if I just sit in my basement all day and make no mistakes,\N{\rChinese}如果我整天坐在地下室里不犯错，我的代理人，民主党国会，都会说：我就是民主党主席。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.06,0:36:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,my surrogates, the Democratic Congress, they're going to be like, oh, I'm going to be the president of the Democratic Party.\N{\rChinese}希拉里·克林顿、比尔·克林顿、巴拉克·奥巴马，…
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.72,0:36:39.66,English,,0,0,0,,Hillary Clinton, Bill Clinton, Barack Obama,\N{\rChinese}Hillary Clinton, BillClinton, Barack Obama,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.84,0:36:42.54,English,,0,0,0,,they'll go out and give speeches for me.\N{\rChinese}他们会出来为我演讲。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.60,0:36:45.86,English,,0,0,0,,They'll fire up the base. And I'll win because\N{\rChinese}他们会点燃基础。于是我赢了，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.86,0:36:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not Trump, okay?\N{\rChinese}我不是特朗普，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.12,0:36:49.68,English,,0,0,0,,That is the entire Biden strategy.\N{\rChinese}那就是完整的拜登策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.24,0:36:51.72,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not Trump.\N{\rChinese}我不是特朗普。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.74,0:37:00.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The problem with this idea is,\N{\rChinese}好吧？这个想法的难点是，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.66,0:37:04.70,English,,0,0,0,,okay, in 2020,\N{\rChinese}好的，2020年，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.04,0:37:08.34,English,,0,0,0,,the American people, the American people, people had four years of Trump,\N{\rChinese}美国人民，美国人民，四年特朗普后，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.48,0:37:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,and they know he sucks, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们知道他很糟，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.40,0:37:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,The problem now is the American people have seen four years of Biden,\N{\rChinese}现在的问题是美国人民已经看到了四年的拜登，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.06,0:37:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,and Biden sucks as well, okay?\N{\rChinese}拜登也很糟，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.08,0:37:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,And so, it's a question like, who sucks more,\N{\rChinese}于是问题是，谁更糟呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.04,0:37:23.14,English,,0,0,0,,Biden or Trump, okay?\N{\rChinese}拜登还是特朗普，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.26,0:37:27.40,English,,0,0,0,,So, in other words, people are not going to come out to vote\N{\rChinese}于是换句话说，选民不会去投票
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.40,0:37:28.94,English,,0,0,0,,because they think both suck,\N{\rChinese}因为他们觉得两者都糟
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.42,0:37:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,and which means that the party with equality, right?\N{\rChinese}并且这意味着拥有平等的党派，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.24,0:37:41.02,English,,0,0,0,,The only coalition with a base that feels more strongly about the issues is going to come out to vote, okay?\N{\rChinese}唯一那支基底更强烈关注议题的联盟才会去投票，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.62,0:37:44.12,English,,0,0,0,,And what we know is that\N{\rChinese}我们已知的就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.12,0:37:48.18,English,,0,0,0,,the Republican coalition\N{\rChinese}共和党联盟
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.18,0:37:51.70,English,,0,0,0,,of rural voters, conservatives, Christians,\N{\rChinese}乡村选民、保守派、基督徒、白人选民
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.42,0:37:54.46,English,,0,0,0,,white voters,\N{\rChinese}white voters,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.66,0:38:00.12,English,,0,0,0,,they feel much more passionately about Trump than the Democratic coalition feels about Biden.\N{\rChinese}他们对特朗普的热情远超民主党联盟对拜登的热情。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.58,0:38:03.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense? So, unfortunately,\N{\rChinese}好吧？这样说对吗？所以不幸的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.38,0:38:06.22,English,,0,0,0,,the answer is that Biden is only going to vote.\N{\rChinese}答案是拜登只会投票。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.24,0:38:10.06,English,,0,0,0,,Biden has no strategy going forward because he didn't have a strategy going forward in 2020.\N{\rChinese}拜登前进没有策略，因为他在2020年也没有前进的策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.58,0:38:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,And he won in 2020, so why can't the same thing happen in,\N{\rChinese}他在2020年赢了，那为什么今年也能这么做呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.24,0:38:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,same thing happen this year, right?\N{\rChinese}同样的事今年也能发生吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.38,0:38:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, because Biden's so old, he's 81,\N{\rChinese}而且不幸的是，拜登年事已高，81岁，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.66,0:38:28.50,English,,0,0,0,,he doesn't have the energy to change the way he is.\N{\rChinese}他没有精力去改变自己的状态。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.60,0:38:32.26,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? It's much easier for him to sit around\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？他坐在那儿更容易，然后祈祷那样的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.26,0:38:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,and pray the way that\N{\rChinese}and pray the waythat
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.52,0:38:39.64,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not Trump will deliver another election than it is for him to go out\N{\rChinese}我不认为特朗普会再赢一次选举，随后再去改变自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.64,0:38:41.70,English,,0,0,0,,and change who he is. He can't change who he is.\N{\rChinese}他自己也没法再改变自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.82,0:38:45.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.62,0:38:48.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, but that's a great question, all right?\N{\rChinese}好的，但这确实是个好问题，没错吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.96,0:38:52.58,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions before?\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.68,0:39:03.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay, so again,\N{\rChinese}好的。好的，再说一次，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.92,0:39:06.72,English,,0,0,0,,I am not sure\N{\rChinese}我不确定
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.72,0:39:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,who will win this year, okay?\N{\rChinese}谁会在今年赢得比赛，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.06,0:39:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,I think it's Trump. I'm not sure that\N{\rChinese}我觉得是特朗普。我不确定尼基·海利会是他的副总统。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.74,0:39:14.40,English,,0,0,0,,Nikki Haley will be his vice president.\N{\rChinese}我只是猜测。所以问题是我们为什么要这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.60,0:39:18.42,English,,0,0,0,,I'm just making a guess. So the question then is why are we doing this?\N{\rChinese}I'm just making a guess. So the question then is why are we doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.54,0:39:21.58,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is this. We try to think.\N{\rChinese}答案就是这样。我们先想一想。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.78,0:39:25.56,English,,0,0,0,,We have to build an analytical model, right, of how the world works.\N{\rChinese}我们得构建一个分析模型，来说明世界是怎样运作的。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.02,0:39:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,And the only way we know if this model works or not is by making predictions\N{\rChinese}检验模型是否有效的唯一办法，就是做出预测。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.04,0:39:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,and testing it against reality.\N{\rChinese}并用它与现实检验。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.88,0:39:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you know what?\N{\rChinese}好吧？那你知道什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.96,0:39:37.18,English,,0,0,0,,It's possible that in August,\N{\rChinese}有可能在八月，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.10,0:39:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,Trump will pick someone else okay?\N{\rChinese}特朗普会选其他人吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.90,0:39:43.12,English,,0,0,0,,Possibly someone named JD Vance okay?\N{\rChinese}可能是叫J.D. Vance的人吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.30,0:39:50.44,English,,0,0,0,,The only thing you need to know about JD Vance is he's very loyal to Trump okay?\N{\rChinese}关于J.D. Vance你只需要知道的一点是他对特朗普非常忠诚。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.52,0:39:53.08,English,,0,0,0,,It's possible he picks JD Vance okay?\N{\rChinese}有可能他选J.D. Vance吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.18,0:39:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,I think he'll pick Nikki Haley. I often actually...\N{\rChinese}我觉得他会选Nikki Haley。我经常这样想……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.96,0:40:02.08,English,,0,0,0,,I often think that there's a very good chance he picks JD Vance as well okay?\N{\rChinese}我经常认为他很可能也会选J.D. Vance，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.08,0:40:04.42,English,,0,0,0,,But I'll make the bet that he picks Nikki Haley.\N{\rChinese}我会押注他会选Nikki Haley。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.90,0:40:09.94,English,,0,0,0,,So it's possible in August he does not pick Nikki Haley,\N{\rChinese}于是，8月他可能不选Nikki Haley，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.04,0:40:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,he picks J.D. Vance or someone else instead.\N{\rChinese}他可能选J.D. Vance或其他人。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.50,0:40:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,It's also possible that in November Trump loses.\N{\rChinese}也有可能在十一月特朗普落败。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.78,0:40:20.70,English,,0,0,0,,Well that's fine because if I'm wrong,\N{\rChinese}好吧，没问题，如果我错了，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.88,0:40:23.62,English,,0,0,0,,then what I do is I go back to this analysis\N{\rChinese}我就回到这份分析里去
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.62,0:40:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,and I make changes to this analysis\N{\rChinese}我对这份分析做了调整
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.00,0:40:30.96,English,,0,0,0,,so that it's much more reflective and accurate.\N{\rChinese}使其更具反思性和准确性。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.96,0:40:32.44,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.56,0:40:39.04,English,,0,0,0,,And that's how we try to think critically about the world.\N{\rChinese}这就是我们尝试用批判性思维看世界的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.14,0:40:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,By building analytical models that we can then test against reality\N{\rChinese}通过构建可随后对照现实检验的分析模型
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.38,0:40:45.60,English,,0,0,0,,and then based on what happens in reality,\N{\rChinese}并根据现实中发生的事来调整
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.88,0:40:49.04,English,,0,0,0,,we can go and refine our analytical model.\N{\rChinese}我们可以去细化我们的分析模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.36,0:40:56.34,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? Okay, so\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.34,0:41:02.28,English,,0,0,0,,next week we discuss the war in Iran,\N{\rChinese}下周我们讨论伊朗的战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.54,0:41:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Because if you look at this,\N{\rChinese}好的？因为如果你看这个，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.34,0:41:09.86,English,,0,0,0,,again if Nikki Haley becomes the vice president,\N{\rChinese}再次，如果尼基·海利成为副总统，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.08,0:41:14.26,English,,0,0,0,,it is very likely she will agitate for war against Iran.\N{\rChinese}很可能她会发动对伊朗的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.04,0:41:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,And Trump will go along, okay?\N{\rChinese}好，特朗普也会跟着走，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.50,0:41:19.32,English,,0,0,0,,And if that's the case, then\N{\rChinese}如果是这样的话，接下来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.32,0:41:23.68,English,,0,0,0,,we need to understand how America will fight the war and how Iran will respond.\N{\rChinese}我们需要了解美国将如何打这场战争，以及伊朗会如何回应。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.02,0:41:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what we will do next week, okay? Thank you.\N{\rChinese}那就是我们下周要做的事，好的？谢谢。
